PlatformIO test directory.

Layout
------
  test/test_native/   Host unit tests (Unity).  Run on the build machine, no
                      board required:

                          pio test -e native

                      Covers the pure-logic modules:
                        - job_log   (test_job_log.cpp)   ring, signature
                                    classification, counters, name tables
                        - log_sink  (test_log_sink.cpp)  ring write/snapshot,
                                    wrap, cursor streaming, tee helpers
                      test_main.cpp owns the Unity runner; test_support.*
                      provides the fake clock + Serial capture.

  test/shims/         Header-only stand-ins (freertos/, esp_timer.h, esp_log.h,
                      Arduino.h) that let the real src/*.cpp compile on the host.
                      Used ONLY by the native env; the firmware build uses the
                      genuine ESP-IDF headers.

The embedded env (esp32-s3-n16r8) sets test_ignore = test_native so a board
test run never tries to build the host-only tests.

Modules with heavy hardware/RTOS coupling (usb_bridge, net_server, http_status)
are not unit-tested here - they are exercised by the on-device end-to-end path
(print a job; inspect /jobs and the :9101 log).

More on PlatformIO Unit Testing:
  https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html
